<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Kragar Frostburn</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-06-28 15:45:10</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Ok, got this spear from a Guildmate when I was L35.  The spear does proc at 35 - so that's the good news.  The bad news is that even with Rising Dexterity and Quickness, the spear procs pretty rarely.  If you're using it in the hopes that it'll proc as often as the gnollhide lariat, you're mistaken.  It is a nice weapon and has a decent damage/second ratio - especially with Quickness on.  It just doesn't proc nearly as often as I'd like...</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Gilbar Shadowpaw</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-07-10 14:44:17</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Ok, here's the scoop: This is dropped in the Library in Kaesora, by "a failed crypt raider". He was green at 49. He spawns with "tortured librarian", who was blue at 49, but dropped fairly easily. But then I had a 47 wiz and a 43 ranger with me. We were owning the zone, with no close calls. I believe that a group of 30's could do quite well in here, with bookoo exp to show for it. Just one thing: KILL THE WARDERS FIRST! They heal. Alot.<BR>
<BR>
The "tortured librarian" seems to drop a kunzar mantle, which nicely replaced my lizard scale mantle. 2 more AC, same wis, and +3 to a 3rd stat (forget which).<BR>
<BR>
The "Spectral Librarian", also blue, drops the Spirit Tome (+6wis/int) and some silly shroud thing which was kinda lame, but sold for 37pp to the vendor.<BR>
<BR>
Be careful when clearing the library, be sure to have 2 healers on hand, and a slower.<BR>
<BR>
Also, the Spectral Guardians drop the spectral pestle, which is used to make the crushed dread diamond for Shaman Cannibalize 2.<BR>
<BR>
Good luck!<BR>
<BR>
Gilbar Shadowpaw,<BR>
49th Shaman of the Tribunal<BR>
Clenched Fist<BR>
Solusek Ro<BR>
<BR>
PS: The only reason I was there was to get the pestle for Cann2. Personally, I like Cann2. I don't care what everybody says =P</font></td></tr></table>
